article_title: Wisconsin Gov. Scott Walker makes GOP presidential campaign stop in Bloomington

article_metadata.description: BLOOMINGTON — For the third time in three years, state Sen. Darin LaHood shared the stage with a presidential candidate at a political rally, introducing Wisconsin Gov. Scott Walker to effusive applause during a Bloomington campaign appearance.LaHood, a Peoria Republican running for his first term in Congress, praised the Badger State’s leader as authentic — “what you see is what you get” — and suggested that Walker’s road map for governing would
article_metadata.author: Chris Kaergard, Peoria Journal Star
